<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">741.13/11–1051</note>
                                <head>No. 316<lb/><hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_TRUMANHS1" type="from">Truman</persName> to
                                        Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1" type="to">Churchill</persName></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d316fn1">The source text was attached to a telegram from the Key
                                        West White House asking that it be sent to Prime Minister
                                            <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName>. A handwritten note on the source text
                                        indicates that it was handed to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_FRANKSSOS1">Franks</persName>’ secretary on
                                        Nov. 11.</note></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">top
                                        secret</hi></seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-10">November 10,
                                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>The January 3 date for our meeting is entirely satisfactory, and
                                    I look forward to seeing you then. I shall also be happy to see
                                    Mr. <persName corresp="#p_EDENA1">Eden</persName>
                                    <pb facs="0748" n="700" xml:id="pg_700"/> again, and will
                                    welcome Lord <persName corresp="#p_ISMAYHL1">Ismay</persName>
                                    and your military advisors.</p>
                                <p>I appreciate your good wishes for Florida sunshine during my stay
                                    at Key West.</p>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>